events.description: The original Nicene Creed is adopted at the First Council of Nicaea.
events.html: • 325 – The original Nicene Creed is adopted at the First Council of Nicaea.[1]

events.description: The Battle of Kalvskinnet takes place outside Nidaros (now Trondheim), Norway. Earl Erling Skakke is killed, and the battle changes the tide of the civil wars.
events.html: • 1179 – The Battle of Kalvskinnet takes place outside Nidaros (now Trondheim), Norway. Earl Erling Skakke is killed, and the battle changes the tide of the civil wars.[2]

events.description: The Earl of Pembroke's army defeats Bruce's Scottish army at the Battle of Methven.
events.html: • 1306 – The Earl of Pembroke's army defeats Bruce's Scottish army at the Battle of Methven.

entities.name: Aymer de Valence, 2nd Earl of Pembroke

events.description: English colonists leave Roanoke Island, after failing to establish England's first permanent settlement in North America.
events.html: • 1586 – English colonists leave Roanoke Island, after failing to establish England's first permanent settlement in North America.

events.description: At least 73,000 people died in the 1718 Tongwei–Gansu earthquake due to landslides in the Qing dynasty.
events.html: • 1718 – At least 73,000 people died in the 1718 Tongwei–Gansu earthquake due to landslides in the Qing dynasty.[3]

events.description: The Boston King's Chapel adopts James Freeman's revised prayer book, without the Nicene Creed, establishing it as the first Unitarian congregation in the United States.
events.html: • 1785 – The Boston King's Chapel adopts James Freeman's revised prayer book, without the Nicene Creed, establishing it as the first Unitarian congregation in the United States.[4][5]

events.description: War of the Second Coalition Battle of Höchstädt results in a French victory over Austria.
events.html: • 1800 – War of the Second Coalition Battle of Höchstädt results in a French victory over Austria.

events.description: The Carlton House Fête is held in London to celebrate the establishment of the Regency era.
events.html: • 1811 – The Carlton House Fête is held in London to celebrate the establishment of the Regency era.[6]

events.description: Battle of Seven Oaks between North West Company and Hudson's Bay Company, near Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada.
events.html: • 1816 – Battle of Seven Oaks between North West Company and Hudson's Bay Company, near Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada.

events.description: Decisive defeat of the Filiki Eteria by the Ottomans at Drăgășani (in Wallachia).
events.html: • 1821 – Decisive defeat of the Filiki Eteria by the Ottomans at Drăgășani (in Wallachia).

events.description: The first officially recorded, organized baseball game is played under Alexander Cartwright's rules on Hoboken, New Jersey's Elysian Fields with the New York Base Ball Club defeating the Knickerbockers 23–1. Cartwright umpired.
events.html: • 1846 – The first officially recorded, organized baseball game is played under Alexander Cartwright's rules on Hoboken, New Jersey's Elysian Fields with the New York Base Ball Club defeating the Knickerbockers 23–1. Cartwright umpired.

entities.name: History of baseball in the United States

events.description: Princess Louise of the Netherlands marries Crown Prince Karl of Sweden–Norway.
events.html: • 1850 – Princess Louise of the Netherlands marries Crown Prince Karl of Sweden–Norway.

events.description: Congress prohibits slavery in all current and future United States territories, and President Lincoln quickly signs the legislation.
events.html: • 1862 – Congress prohibits slavery in all current and future United States territories, and President Lincoln quickly signs the legislation.

events.description: Over two years after the Emancipation Proclamation, slaves in Galveston, Texas, United States, are officially informed of their freedom. The anniversary was officially celebrated in Texas and other states as Juneteenth. On June 17, 2021, Juneteenth officially became a federal holiday in the United States.
events.html: • 1865 – Over two years after the Emancipation Proclamation, slaves in Galveston, Texas, United States, are officially informed of their freedom. The anniversary was officially celebrated in Texas and other states as Juneteenth. On June 17, 2021, Juneteenth officially became a federal holiday in the United States.

entities.name: Federal holidays in the United States

events.description: Maximilian I of the Second Mexican Empire is executed by a firing squad in Querétaro, Querétaro.
events.html: • 1867 – Maximilian I of the Second Mexican Empire is executed by a firing squad in Querétaro, Querétaro.

events.description: The Herzegovinian rebellion against the Ottoman Empire begins.
events.html: • 1875 – The Herzegovinian rebellion against the Ottoman Empire begins.

events.description: Benito Mussolini, at the time a radical Socialist, is arrested by Bern police for advocating a violent general strike.
events.html: • 1903 – Benito Mussolini, at the time a radical Socialist, is arrested by Bern police for advocating a violent general strike.

events.description: The first Father's Day is celebrated in Spokane, Washington.
events.html: • 1910 – The first Father's Day is celebrated in Spokane, Washington.

events.description: Natives Land Act, 1913 in South Africa implemented.
events.html: • 1913 – Natives Land Act, 1913 in South Africa implemented.

events.description: The village of Knockcroghery, Ireland, is burned by British forces.
events.html: • 1921 – The village of Knockcroghery, Ireland, is burned by British forces.[7]

events.description: The Communications Act of 1934 establishes the United States' Federal Communications Commission (FCC).
events.html: • 1934 – The Communications Act of 1934 establishes the United States' Federal Communications Commission (FCC).

events.description: The Philadelphia Eagles and Pittsburgh Steelers of the NFL merge for one season due to player shortages caused by World War II.
events.html: • 1943 – The Philadelphia Eagles and Pittsburgh Steelers of the NFL merge for one season due to player shortages caused by World War II.

events.description: Pan Am Flight 121 crashes in the Syrian Desert near Mayadin, Syria, killing 15 and injuring 21.
events.html: • 1947 – Pan Am Flight 121 crashes in the Syrian Desert near Mayadin, Syria, killing 15 and injuring 21.[8]

events.description: Cold War: Julius and Ethel Rosenberg are executed at Sing Sing, in New York.
events.html: • 1953 – Cold War: Julius and Ethel Rosenberg are executed at Sing Sing, in New York.[9]

events.description: Charlotte Motor Speedway holds its first NASCAR race, the inaugural World 600.
events.html: • 1960 – Charlotte Motor Speedway holds its first NASCAR race, the inaugural World 600.

events.description: Kuwait declares independence from the United Kingdom.
events.html: • 1961 – Kuwait declares independence from the United Kingdom.

events.description: The Civil Rights Act of 1964 is approved after surviving an 83-day filibuster in the United States Senate.
events.html: • 1964 – The Civil Rights Act of 1964 is approved after surviving an 83-day filibuster in the United States Senate.

events.description: Nguyễn Cao Kỳ becomes Prime Minister of South Vietnam at the head of a military junta; General Nguyễn Văn Thiệu becomes the figurehead chief of state.
events.html: • 1965 – Nguyễn Cao Kỳ becomes Prime Minister of South Vietnam at the head of a military junta; General Nguyễn Văn Thiệu becomes the figurehead chief of state.

events.description: Garfield's first comic strip, originally published locally as Jon in 1976, goes into nationwide syndication.
events.html: • 1978 – Garfield's first comic strip, originally published locally as Jon in 1976, goes into nationwide syndication.[10]

events.description: Members of the Revolutionary Party of Central American Workers, dressed as Salvadoran soldiers, attack the Zona Rosa area of San Salvador.
events.html: • 1985 – Members of the Revolutionary Party of Central American Workers, dressed as Salvadoran soldiers, attack the Zona Rosa area of San Salvador.

entities.name: Revolutionary Party of Central American Workers

events.description: Basque separatist group ETA commits one of its most violent attacks, in which a bomb is set off in a supermarket, Hipercor, killing 21 and injuring 45.
events.html: • 1987 – Basque separatist group ETA commits one of its most violent attacks, in which a bomb is set off in a supermarket, Hipercor, killing 21 and injuring 45.

events.description: Aeroflot Flight N-528 crashes at Berdiansk Airport in present-day Ukraine, killing eight people.
events.html: • 1987 – Aeroflot Flight N-528 crashes at Berdiansk Airport in present-day Ukraine, killing eight people.[11]

events.description: Pope John Paul II canonizes 117 Vietnamese Martyrs.
events.html: • 1988 – Pope John Paul II canonizes 117 Vietnamese Martyrs.

events.description: The current international law defending indigenous peoples, Indigenous and Tribal Peoples Convention, 1989, is ratified for the first time by Norway.
events.html: • 1990 – The current international law defending indigenous peoples, Indigenous and Tribal Peoples Convention, 1989, is ratified for the first time by Norway.

events.description: The Communist Party of the Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic is founded in Moscow.
events.html: • 1990 – The Communist Party of the Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic is founded in Moscow.

entities.name: Communist Party of the Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic

events.description: The last Soviet army units in Hungary are withdrawn.
events.html: • 1991 – The last Soviet army units in Hungary are withdrawn.

events.description: Following a series of Michelin tire failures during the United States Grand Prix weekend at Indianapolis, and without an agreement being reached, 14 cars from seven teams in Michelin tires withdrew after completing the formation lap, leaving only six cars from three teams on Bridgestone tires to race.
events.html: • 2005 – Following a series of Michelin tire failures during the United States Grand Prix weekend at Indianapolis, and without an agreement being reached, 14 cars from seven teams in Michelin tires withdrew after completing the formation lap, leaving only six cars from three teams on Bridgestone tires to race.[12]

events.description: The al-Khilani Mosque bombing in Baghdad leaves 78 people dead and another 218 injured.
events.html: • 2007 – The al-Khilani Mosque bombing in Baghdad leaves 78 people dead and another 218 injured.

events.description: Mass riots involving over 10,000 people and 10,000 police officers break out in Shishou, China, over the dubious circumstances surrounding the death of a local chef.
events.html: • 2009 – Mass riots involving over 10,000 people and 10,000 police officers break out in Shishou, China, over the dubious circumstances surrounding the death of a local chef.

events.description: War in North-West Pakistan: The Pakistani Armed Forces open Operation Rah-e-Nijat against the Taliban and other Islamist rebels in the South Waziristan area of the Federally Administered Tribal Areas.
events.html: • 2009 – War in North-West Pakistan: The Pakistani Armed Forces open Operation Rah-e-Nijat against the Taliban and other Islamist rebels in the South Waziristan area of the Federally Administered Tribal Areas.

events.description: WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange requests asylum in London's Ecuadorian Embassy for fear of extradition to the US after publication of previously classified documents including footage of civilian killings by the US army.
events.html: • 2012 – WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange requests asylum in London's Ecuadorian Embassy for fear of extradition to the US after publication of previously classified documents including footage of civilian killings by the US army.
